Mexico ' s Grupo Marino to export cappuccino coffee . Grupo Marino , coffee industrialists with 6 percent of the Mexican soluble market , will export a new product this year , a director said Tuesday . " The product will be a cappuccino coffee for vending machines , " Javier Lizarraga Mercado , the vice - chairman of the group ' s coffee unit Cafe Marino said , adding the company was investing close to $ 1 . 5 million in the project . The cappuccino coffee will be sold by the U . S . company Chock Full O ' Nuts , mainly in the Unites States but also in Ireland and part of Denmark . The two formed an joint venture alliance in 1994 . ( ( - - Monica Ballesca , Guadalajara bureau ( 523 ) 817 - 0397 ) ) 
